---
description: Frontend wiring rules (apps/web, apps/web-next)
globs: apps/web/**,apps/web-next/**
---

Full detail: [docs/agents/frontend.md](../../docs/agents/frontend.md).

- The frontends are wiring references, not product UI. Each has its own package.json + lockfile.
- No tests here (per project direction) — the 90% floor is backend-only.
- Never store tokens/secrets in localStorage (module memory in the sample; httpOnly-cookie BFF in prod).
- API base URL from env (`VITE_API_URL` / Next env); prefer same-origin `/api` via the proxy.
- Don't import `@clevrook/*` backend libs into a frontend. Keep Dockerfile/railway.json wiring intact.
- Exact-pinned deps + committed lockfile.
